704908f-a.text:
Hicks Street, west side, south from Middagh Street.  Also seen is Middagh Street, south side, west from Hicks Street.  The corner building in 1870 was occupied by the Henry Walters Grocery; prior to this it was a stable for the Williamsburg bakery. The building was still in use in 1929.
April 1925

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

705713f-b.text:
74 Middagh Street, south side, west of Henry Street. This build- ing housed Engine Co. No. 3, until 1869, when the volunteer fire-corp was replaced by a municipally paid system. It was subsequently converted into a 4-story family house. In 1875, at was purchased by Jacob Ring who converted the first floor into a store; it was demol ished before 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
